The projection operator \(P^a_b = \delta^a_b + U^a U_b\) for a 4-velocity \(U^a\) (with \(U^a U_a = -1\)) projects vectors onto the subspace orthogonal to \(U^a\). For an arbitrary timelike vector \(V^a\) that is not necessarily normalized, the operator must be modified to ensure it still projects orthogonally to \(V^a\). The required modification is to include a minus sign and divide by the norm squared of \(V^a\), yielding \(P^a_b = \delta^a_b - \frac{V^a V_b}{V^c V_c}\). This ensures \(P^a_b V^b = 0\) and retains the idempotent and projection properties.

\boxed{P^a_b = \delta^a_b - \frac{V^a V_b}{V^c V_c}}
